org.ndnx.ndn.protocol
Class Interest

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.impl.encoding.GenericXMLEncodable
      org.ndnx.ndn.protocol.Interest
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Comparable<Interest>, XMLEncodable, ContentNameProvider
public class Interest
extends GenericXMLEncodable
implements XMLEncodable, Comparable<Interest>, Cloneable, ContentNameProvider

Represents a NDN Interest packet, and performs all the allowed specializations of queries recognized and supported by them. cf. ContentObject Implements Comparable to make it easy to store in a Set and avoid duplicates.

                       PublisherPublicKeyDigest resultPublisherKeyID)
Determine whether a piece of content's name *without* digest component matches this Interest. This doesn't match if the digest is specified in the Interest.

encode

public void encode(XMLEncoder encoder)
            throws ContentEncodingException
Description copied from interface: XMLEncodable
Encode this object during an ongoing encoding pass; this is what subclasses generally need to know how to implement. Writes just the object itself, higher-level processes have handled start and end document if need be. Allows object to be written using the same code whether it is a top-level element written alone, or nested inside another element.

Specified by:
encode in interface XMLEncodable
Specified by:
encode in class GenericXMLEncodable
Parameters:
encoder - the encoder being used; encapsulates state including the codec being used as well as the output destination and current offset
Throws:
ContentEncodingException
